This paper deals with the enumeration of answers to MSO queries on trees, which is a problem in the area of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses techniques for maintaining an index under node relabelings, which is a topic in the area of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions practical query languages such as aggregate, group-by, and parameterized queries, which are topics in the areas of databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses circuit-based enumeration structures, which is a topic in the area of computational complexity (cs.CC).
